frameDefinitions: An Agent actively (yet not always with success) attempts to keep themselves from participating in an Event.
A Potential_hindrance or an Agent (via their actions) keeps an Event from taking place, or despite the possibility of prevent the Event, do not do so.
A Protagonist is awake at some Time and Place.
This frame contains nouns denoting Aggregates of Individuals.
In this frame a Preventing_cause interferes with the ability of a Protagonist to complete an intended Action.
frameExamples: Rain <t>prevented</t> the ball game from taking place.
Carolyn <t>abandoned</t> her car and jumped on a red double decker bus.
An <t><fex name='Agg'>army</fex></t> of postal workers descended on my office.
listRoleDefinitions: The Agent who tries to keep an Event from taking place.
The Event is the action or state of affairs that the Agent wishes to prevent.
The <fen>Time</fen> is when the <fen>Agent</fen> prevents the <fen>Event</fen> from taking place.
The <fen>Place </fen> is where the <fen>Agent</fen> attempts to prevent the <fen>Event</fen> from taking place.
The <fen>Potential_hindrance</fen> is the force which keeps the <fen>Event</fen> from happening, or does not.
The <fen>Event</fen> is prevented from occurring by the <fen>Preventing_cause</fen> or the <fen>Agent</fen>.
The <fen>Agent</fen> is the sentient being which keeps the <fen>Event</fen> from happening.
The <fen>Time</fen> is when the <fen>Potential_hindrance</fen> or <fen>Agent</fen> keeps the <fen>Event</fen> from taking place.
The <fen>Place</fen> is where the <fen>Potential_hindrance</fen> or <fen>Agent</fen> keeps the <fen>Event</fen> from taking place.
The entity that is not sleeping.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Protagonist</fen> is awake.
Where the event takes place.
The <fex name='Agent'>Agent</fex> is the person who acts to leave behind the <fen>Theme</fen>.
The <fex name='Theme'>Theme</fex> is the entity that is relinguished to no one from the <fex name='Agent'>Agent</fex>'s possession.
When the <fen>Agent</fen> gives up the <fen>Theme</fen>.
The location where the <fen>Agent</fen> gives up the <fen>Theme</fen>.
This role identifies the people or things that form  the <fen>Aggregate</fen>.
This role identifies the collection of entities that are the <fen>Aggregate</fen>.
The <fen>Preventing_cause</fen> is the agent or force who keeps the <fen>Protagonist</fen> from completing her or his planned <fen>Action</fen>.
The <fen>Protagonist</fen> is the individual or group of individuals who have a planned <fen>Action</fen> which is prevented by the <fen>Preventing_cause</fen>
The <fen>Action</fen> is the action or event certain individuals desire to bring about which is prevented by the <fen>Preventing_cause</fen>.
The <fen>Time</fen> is when the thwarting occurs.
The <fen>Place</fen> is where the thwarting occurs.
listRoleExamples: <fex>She</fex> was awake through the whole football game.
A crowd <fex>of hoodlums</fex> filled the plaza.
A <fex><t>crowd</t></fex> of hoodlums filled the plaza.
